<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-01T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-01T13:00:00-05:00" n="595" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">647.116/147a: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul at Melbourne</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dye</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-01T14:00:00-04:00">June
                                        1, 1936—2 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>For Moffat. You may use the sense of my May 27, 5 p.m. in any
                                conversations you have but not for publication at the present time.
                                You may, however, keep the idea in mind and let us have any
                                suggestions you may have with regard to publicity if you consider it
                                advisable.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>